        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10802",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For security reasons, particulary with the File backend, I prefer keep this (little) slowdown than taking a risk of nasty things (even with get()) \n\nsorry :(",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T04:30:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T04:30:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10806",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Can you explain what nasty things you are talking about? And why specific backend can't take care of it if it needs to?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T10:55:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T10:55:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10807",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For example :\n\n- if the cache id is taken from an url like \"foo.php?id=bar\"\n\nAND\n\n- if you use the File backend\n\nAND\n\n- if you call a get($_GET['id'])\n\nmaybe if a craker play with URL like\n\nfoo.php?id=..\/..\/..\/..\/etc\/passwd\n\nit could be possible to get a security problem\n\nTo be honnest, I don't want to deal with things like that in the File backend. So tag and cache id (which are used to make the cache filename) must be safe and filtered by the Core\n\nSame thing with the Sqlite backend. I don't want SQL injection problems even if the real error (get a cache id from $_GET without a solid filter) is not in Zend_Cache.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T14:10:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T14:10:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10808",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "OK, but then if you need something like checking if there's only alphanumeric characters there won't it be faster to use something like strspn\/strcspn?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T15:25:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T15:25:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10809",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't know but if you make some benchs, I'm really interested in the results :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T16:41:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T16:41:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "OK, I did some tests, and indeed strspn is about twice as fast as preg, but there's a catch - AFAIK there's no function that returns \"if there are characters not from this list\" - strspn returns length of correct string, which has to be compared to length of the original, and this means another function call, which eats up all speedup achieved by strspn. So unless there's some clever function that can do \"check if there's only these chars in a string\" with one fcall without regexp - preg_match is the best. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-11T13:36:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-11T13:36:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10813",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "nice work :-) even results are not good for now :-(",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-11T16:34:16.000+0000",
